(5071, '', '', 'The Beach at Honfleur', 'France, 1840-1926', 'European Painting', 'Claude Monet', '', 'Framed:  34 1/4 x 43 x 3 3/4 in. (87 x 109.22 x 87 cm)', '', 'France, 1864-1866', 'Oil on canvas', 'http://collections.lacma.org/sites/default/files/remote_images/piction/ma-31769857-WEB.jpg', 'Gift of Mrs. Reese Hale Taylor (64.4)', 'Claude Monet made this painting in 1864, in the early years of the movement that came to be known as Impressionism. The painting, with its broken brushstrokes designed to capture the fleeting effects of light, is a hallmark of Impressionism.<br><br>Press the play button below to find out why the painting was so novel for its day, as you look at it more closely.<br><br><script src=http://cdnapi.kaltura.com/p/491681/sp/49168100/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/6232402/partner_id/491681></script> <object id=kaltura_player_1375413461 name=kaltura_player_1375413461 type=application/x-shockwave-flash allowFullScreen=true allowNetworking=all allowScriptAccess=always height=30 width=300 bgcolor=#000000 style=width: 300px; height: 30px; xmlns:dc=http://purl.org/dc/terms/ xmlns:media=http://search.yahoo.com/searchmonkey/media/ rel=media:video resource=http://cdnapi.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1375413461/wid/_491681/uiconf_id/6232402/entry_id/0_j8s18iqr data=http://cdnapi.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1375413461/wid/_491681/uiconf_id/6232402/entry_id/0_j8s18iqr>  <param name=allowFullScreen value=true />  <param name=allowNetworking value=all />  <param name=allowScriptAccess value=always />  <param name=bgcolor value=#000000 />  <param name=flashVars value= />  <param name=movie value=http://cdnapi.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1375413461/wid/_491681/uiconf_id/6232402/entry_id/0_j8s18iqr />    <a rel=media:thumbnail href=></a>  <span property=dc:description content=></span>  <span property=media:title content=STOP1_MONET.wav></span>  <span property=media:width content=300></span>  <span property=media:height content=30></spa